# Frontend (Visionary)

Source of truth: `docs/design.md` — Layout, Typography, Motion, Component Foundations, Elevation.

## Responsive Layout

- **Mobile-first.** Add complexity at `md` (768px) and above.
- Breakpoints only: `sm` 640, `md` 768, `lg` 1024, `xl` 1280, `2xl` 1536 — no custom breakpoints without approval.
- Page shells: `container.*`. Forms/articles: `content.*` (narrow 560, reading 680, wide 960).
- Grid: **12 columns**; single column below `md`; max **2 nested grid levels**.
- Gutters/margins: `spacing.4` / `spacing.6` / `spacing.8` per spec.

## Typography

- **Display** (Playfair): headings and hero only
- **Reading** (Lora): body copy — max **65ch**, optimal **60ch** for long text
- **Interface** (DM Sans): labels, buttons, inputs, metadata
- Use named steps: `hero`, `heading-xl|lg|md|sm`, `body-lg`, `body`, `label`, `caption` — **14px minimum** for UI text (`label` and `caption` are both 14px; differentiate with weight).
- Max **three type levels** per screen; prefer weight over size for sub-hierarchy

## Spacing & Radius

Use `spacing.1–24` scale only. Recommended: inline 1–2, component padding 3–4, sections 8–12.

Radius: `sm` inputs, `md` buttons/alerts, `lg` cards/modals, `pill` for pills only.

## Elevation & Layering

- `elevation.card` (z-index 1), `elevation.dropdown` (100), `elevation.overlay` (150), `elevation.modal` (200)
- One modal level max; no nested elevated cards

## Motion

- Durations: `instant|fast|normal|slow` from spec
- Easing: `standard` default; `enter` on show, `exit` on hide
- Animate **opacity and transform** only — not width/height/top unless required
- Always provide reduced-motion fallback (see `accessibility.mdc`)

## Component Foundations

Implement Button, Input, Card, Alert, Modal using **component token slots** from `docs/design.md`:

- Button: one primary per section; destructive needs confirmation; use `action.destructive*` not `status.error*` for actions
- Input: errors use `status.error.*`; disabled not focusable
- Alert: status communication only — not CTAs
- Modal: scrim `overlay.scrim`, focus trap, explicit cancel/confirm for destructive flows
